article.headline: Morgan St. 85, Howard 62
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Jamar Smith scored 20 points, Joseph McLean had 18 points and seven rebounds, and Morgan State defeated Howard, 85-62 Monday night. Reggie Holmes scored 16 points, Ronald Timus had 14 points and Jerrel Green had eight points and 13 assists for Morgan (12-15, 10-6 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), which shot 72 percent in the second half and 56.9 percent for the game. Darek Mitchell scored 17 points and Darryl Hudson had 10 to lead Howard (9-19, 5-11). Morgan started to pull away in the second half as they opened with a 13-3 run, including two three-pointers from McLean, to take a 48-32 lead with 16:55 remaining. Howard eventually rallied back with a 7-0 spurt and pulled within 53-44 following a three-pointer from Will Gant with 12:05 remaining. Morgan, though, answered by outscoring the Bison, 32-18, the rest of the game. Smith helped Morgan take command of the game late in the first half as he scored nine of the Bears' final 14 points which gave his team a 35-29 lead going into intermission. Howard never led by more than two points in the first half as Morgan committed just four turnovers during that span. The Bison stayed close in the first half as they connected on 5-for-9 three-point shot attempts. However, Howard hurt itself at the free-throw line where the Bison missed 7 of 11 attempts in the first 20 minutes. They finished the game going just 8-for-18 from the free-throw line.
